    "url": "https://www.tiktok.com/@sivanstravels/video/7662426140996373773",
    "post_id": "7662426140996373773",
    "description": "Everything you need to do on a trip to Lisbon ✨ You can do all of this in 3-4 days! Save for your trip ✈️ #lisbontravel #visitlisbon #eurosummer\nExplore Lisbon's must-see attractions and activities in just 3-4 days. Plan your perfect trip now! ✈️ #lisbontravel #visitlisbon #eurosummer\nLisbon, the stunning capital of Portugal, offers a rich blend of history, culture, and stunning landscapes. Planning a trip to Lisbon can be an exciting endeavor, and with just 3-4 days, you can experience the best it has to offer. Here’s a comprehensive guide to ensure you make the most out of your Lisbon adventure.\n\nStart your journey in the historic district of Alfama, one of Lisbon's oldest neighborhoods. Wander through its narrow streets and soak in the charming atmosphere, exploring iconic landmarks like the São Jorge Castle that provides breathtaking views of the city. Make sure to capture a few photos of the colorful buildings and traditional azulejos (ceramic tiles) that decorate the streets.\n\nNext, head to Belém, where you can delve into Portugal’s maritime history at the Jerónimos Monastery and the Tower of Belém, both UNESCO World Heritage Sites. Don’t forget to try the renowned Pastéis de Belém, a must-eat pastry that will tantalize your taste buds.\n\nFor art aficionados, the Calouste Gulbenkian Museum houses an impressive collection ranging from ancient to modern works. For contemporary art, the MAAT (Museum of Art, Architecture and Technology) offers intriguing exhibitions in a stunning architectural space by the river.\n\nShopping and dining in Lisbon are experiences of their own. The Chiado and Bairro Alto neighborhoods are filled with boutiques, cafés, and restaurants. Enjoy local cuisines, from fresh seafood to the famous bacalhau (codfish).\n\nAs your trip winds down, take a tram ride on the historic Tram 28, giving you a unique view of the city's charming neighborhoods. With its lively atmosphere and vibrant nightlife, ending your day in one of Lisbon's Fado houses is an experience to cherish.\n\nOverall, Lisbon is a city that can easily enchant visitors. With these tips in hand, you can fully immerse yourself in its charm over a span of just 3-4 days. Pack your bags and get ready for an unforgettable journey! ✈️",
